e valeurs sont manquantes (les NaN) dans les colonnes critiques comme les compétences (list_skills) et simule la répartition des échecs et succès pour anticiper le nettoyage.*"],"metadata":{"id":"7Y60prnM8hZ2"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# 1. Count missing values in the 'list_skills' feature\n","print(\"Missing values in list_skills:\", df_17['list_skills'].isna().sum())\n","\n","# 2. Diagnostic of the strict binarization on the 'correct' target\n","print(\"\\nSimulation of 'correct' values after strict binarization:\")\n","simulation_correct = (df_17['correct'] == 1.0).astype(int)\n","print(simulation_correct.value_counts(dropna=False))\n","\n","# 3. Count missing values in response times\n","print(\"\\nMissing values in response time:\", df_17['ms_first_response_time'].isna().sum())"],"metadata":{"id":"Dee2li71rVkL","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390622545,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":83,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"46e625bb-071d-4874-83ec-cfc2a929b1fe"},"execution_count":6,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Missing values in list_skills: 301330\n","\n","Simulation of 'correct' values after strict binarization:\n","correct\n","1    308050\n","0    191950\n","Name: count, dtype: int64\n","\n","Missing values in response time: 123\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Étape 4 : Nettoyage Rigoureux (Missing Values & Consistency)**"],"metadata":{"id":"unVG0TSgy1zC"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Purger la base de données de ses anomalies. La cellule supprime les lignes sans compétences étiquetées (indispensable pour la future explicabilité XAI) et transforme la colonne de score (correct) en un format binaire strict (1 pour succès total, 0 pour le reste).*"],"metadata":{"id":"iAfBfujpzBLI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# A. Processing 'list_skills' (Knowledge Components)\n","# Drop rows with missing skills and explicitly CREATE A COPY to prevent SettingWithCopyWarning\n","df_clean = df_17.dropna(subset=['list_skills']).copy()\n","\n","# B. Processing the 'correct' target: Strict binarization\n","# Only a perfect score of 1.0 maps to 1, any partial or incorrect score maps to 0\n","df_clean['correct'] = (df_clean['correct'] == 1.0).astype(int)\n","\n","# C. Type conversion and cleaning for response time\n","df_clean['ms_first_response_time'] = pd.to_numeric(df_clean['ms_first_response_time'], errors='coerce')\n","df_clean = df_clean.dropna(subset=['ms_first_response_time'])\n","\n","# Data Health Verification (Sanity Check)\n","print(f\"Initial rows: {len(df_17)}\")\n","print(f\"Rows after cleaning: {len(df_clean)}\")\n","print(f\"Percentage retained: {(len(df_clean)/len(df_17))*100:.2f}%\")"],"metadata":{"id":"hprbtBEDy4Et","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390622722,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":170,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"9342238b-64bc-48fa-b62e-2a896251ce2d"},"execution_count":7,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Initial rows: 500000\n","Rows after cleaning: 198662\n","Percentage retained: 39.73%\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Étape 5 : Sequential Feature Engineering (Historical Context)**"],"metadata":{"id":"6pshbe0SrGJg"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Créer de nouvelles variables d'apprentissage (Feature Engineering) qui mesurent l'évolution de l'étudiant dans le temps (historique des tentatives, précision passée, score de gamification). Le code est conçu avec des décalages mathématiques stricts pour empêcher le modèle de lire l'avenir (\"Data Leakage\"). Il calcule aussi la difficulté dynamique des exercices et encode les textes en valeurs numériques (One-Hot Encoding).*"],"metadata":{"id":"LVajOzGc-Dp7"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","# 1. Ensure strict chronological order before sequential calculations\n","df_clean = df_clean.sort_values(by='order_id').reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","# 2. Calculate past attempts for each user on each specific skill\n","df_clean['past_attempts'] = df_clean.groupby(['user_id', 'list_skills']).cumcount()\n","\n","# 3. Calculate past successes strictly avoiding data leakage\n","# (Subtracting the current row's 'correct' value ensures the model doesn't see the future)\n","cumulative_success = df_clean.groupby(['user_id', 'list_skills'])['correct'].cumsum()\n","df_clean['past_successes'] = cumulative_success - df_clean['correct']\n","\n","# 4. Calculate historical accuracy (handling division by zero for the first attempt)\n","df_clean['historical_accuracy'] = np.where(\n","    df_clean['past_attempts'] > 0,\n","    df_clean['past_successes'] / df_clean['past_attempts'],\n","    0.0\n",")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 5. GAMIFICATION CONCEPT INTEGRATION\n","# ==========================================\n","# Define gamification rules (rewards and penalties)\n","REWARD_POINTS = 10\n","PENALTY_POINTS = -5\n","\n","# Assign points earned or lost for each interaction\n","df_clean['points_earned'] = np.where(df_clean['correct'] == 1, REWARD_POINTS, PENALTY_POINTS)\n","\n","# Calculate cumulative score strictly avoiding data leakage\n","# Note: No need to re-sort by user_id here. The global chronological sort from Step 1 is preserved,\n","# and pandas groupby cumsum() handles user-specific accumulation automatically.\n","cumulative_score = df_clean.groupby('user_id')['points_earned'].cumsum()\n","\n","# Subtract the current row's points to ensure the score represents the strictly past state\n","df_clean['gamification_score'] = cumulative_score - df_clean['points_earned']\n","\n","# Optional: Prevent the score from dropping below zero (common in gamification)\n","# df_clean['gamification_score'] = df_clean['gamification_score'].clip(lower=0)\n","\n","# Clean up: drop the temporary column\n","df_clean = df_clean.drop(columns=['points_earned'])\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 5.BIS: GAMIFICATION - MAGIC HINTS (FOR SUBJECT 2 XAI)\n","# ==========================================\n","# Simulating the use of hints logically based on the student's effort\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","def generate_magic_hints(row):\n","    if row['correct'] == 1 and row['past_attempts'] == 0:\n","        return np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.90, 0.10]) # Quick success = rarely uses a hint\n","    elif row['correct'] == 1 and row['past_attempts'] > 0:\n","        return np.random.choice([0, 1, 2], p=[0.20, 0.50, 0.30]) # Success after effort = likely used hints\n","    else:\n","        return np.random.choice([0, 1, 2, 3], p=[0.30, 0.20, 0.30, 0.20]) # Failure = stuck or gave up\n","\n","df_clean['magic_hint_count'] = df_clean.apply(generate_magic_hints, axis=1)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 6. DATA TYPES IDENTIFICATION PHASE\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"--- Data Types Identification ---\")\n","print(df_clean.dtypes)\n","print(\"---------------------------------\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 7. SAVE TO GOOGLE DRIVE\n","# ==========================================\n","output_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_engineered.csv'\n","df_clean.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n","\n","# 8. Sanity check: Display the new temporal features including gamification\n","print(\"\\nSanity Check - Engineered Features:\")\n","columns_to_show = ['user_id', 'list_skills', 'correct', 'past_attempts', 'historical_accuracy', 'gamification_score']\n","print(df_clean[columns_to_show].head(10))"],"metadata":{"id":"ZejHkSPOrqNu","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390647209,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":24480,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"23cef82b-35ea-48bb-cfa5-e1fa4bf5a3c1"},"execution_count":8,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["--- Data Types Identification ---\n","order_id                    int64\n","assignment_id               int64\n","user_id                     int64\n","assistment_id               int64\n","problem_id                  int64\n","original                    int64\n","correct                     int64\n","attempt_count               int64\n","ms_first_response_time    float64\n","tutor_mode                 object\n","answer_type                object\n","sequence_id                 int64\n","position                    int64\n","problem_set_type           object\n","base_sequence_id            int64\n","list_skill_ids             object\n","list_skills                object\n","past_attempts               int64\n","past_successes              int64\n","historical_accuracy       float64\n","gamification_score          int64\n","magic_hint_count            int64\n","dtype: object\n","---------------------------------\n","\n","Sanity Check - Engineered Features:\n","   user_id                           list_skills  correct  past_attempts  \\\n","0    78068                            Mean;Table        0              0   \n","1    63205  Multiplication and Division Integers        1              0   \n","2    70759                  Probability Compound        0              0   \n","3    70759                  Probability Compound        0              1   \n","4    70759                  Probability Compound        1              2   \n","5    70759                  Probability Compound        1              3   \n","6    70759                  Probability Compound        1              4   \n","7    70759                          Median;Table        0              0   \n","8    70759                          Median;Table        1              1   \n","9    70759                          Median;Table        1              2   \n","\n","   historical_accuracy  gamification_score  \n","0             0.000000                   0  \n","1             0.000000                   0  \n","2             0.000000                   0  \n","3             0.000000                  -5  \n","4             0.000000                 -10  \n","5             0.333333                   0  \n","6             0.500000                  10  \n","7             0.000000                  20  \n","8             0.000000                  15  \n","9             0.500000                  25  \n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Analyse de l'évolution du système; Il calcule automatiquement la difficulté de chaque exercice en fonction des échecs passés des autres élèves, puis transforme les catégories de texte (comme le type de réponse) en formats numériques compréhensibles par la machine."],"metadata":{"id":"7YJhq5dwAF9D"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","# A. Dynamic Item Difficulty (Strictly avoiding data leakage)\n","# 1. Count global past attempts for the specific problem\n","df_clean['problem_attempts'] = df_clean.groupby('problem_id').cumcount()\n","\n","# 2. Calculate cumulative correct answers globally (excluding current row)\n","cumulative_problem_success = df_clean.groupby('problem_id')['correct'].cumsum()\n","df_clean['problem_past_success'] = cumulative_problem_success - df_clean['correct']\n","\n","# 3. Calculate dynamic difficulty: 1 - (past_success / past_attempts)\n","# Higher value = harder problem. Default to 0.5 for the very first encounter.\n","df_clean['item_difficulty'] = np.where(\n","    df_clean['problem_attempts'] > 0,\n","    1 - (df_clean['problem_past_success'] / df_clean['problem_attempts']),\n","    0.5\n",")\n","\n","# B. XAI Preparation: One-Hot Encoding for your specific categorical features\n","# We select the textual features from your list of 17\n","categorical_cols = ['tutor_mode', 'answer_type', 'problem_set_type', 'original']\n","\n","# Apply One-Hot Encoding\n","# drop_first=True is essential to avoid the dummy variable trap in XAI analysis\n","df_clean = pd.get_dummies(df_clean, columns=categorical_cols, drop_first=True, dtype=int)\n","\n","# C. Cleanup CORRIGÉ (On garde list_skills pour l'injection de dérive plus tard)\n","columns_to_drop = ['problem_attempts', 'problem_past_success', 'list_skill_ids']\n","df_final = df_clean.drop(columns=[col for col in columns_to_drop if col in df_clean.columns])\n","\n","# D. Save the final engineered dataset ready for XAI and Drift analysis\n","output_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_engineered_final.csv'\n","df_final.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n","\n","# E. Sanity Check\n","print(\"Feature Engineering & XAI Prep Completed Successfully.\")\n","print(f\"Final shape: {df_final.shape}\")\n","print(\"\\nNew columns created (sample):\")\n","print([col for col in df_final.columns if 'answer_type' in col or 'item_difficulty' in col][:5])"],"metadata":{"id":"hUkt4sqR2MND","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390650191,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":3003,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"41893a88-2777-448c-98bf-0ee0dcc8105e"},"execution_count":9,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Feature Engineering & XAI Prep Completed Successfully.\n","Final shape: (198662, 27)\n","\n","New columns created (sample):\n","['item_difficulty', 'answer_type_choose_1', 'answer_type_fill_in_1', 'answer_type_open_response']\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## ** Etape 6 :Normalisation des données (Feature Scaling)**"],"metadata":{"id":"deVGhjOf2mS8"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Mettre toutes les variables numériques sur la même échelle mathématique (moyenne de 0, écart-type de 1) via le StandardScaler. Cela empêche les grandes valeurs (comme le temps de réponse en millisecondes) d'écraser les petites valeurs (comme le score binaire) lors de l'entraînement, et garantit que l'algorithme SHAP (XAI) attribuera son importance de manière équitable.*"],"metadata":{"id":"Hlk61rGNKUh4"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n","\n","# 1. Identify the numerical continuous features to scale\n","# We exclude IDs and binary/one-hot encoded columns\n","continuous_features = [\n","    'ms_first_response_time',\n","    'past_attempts',\n","    'past_successes',\n","    'historical_accuracy',\n","    'item_difficulty',\n","    'gamification_score', # <--- AJOUT DU SCORE DE GAMIFICATION ICI\n","    'magic_hint_count'\n","]\n","\n","# 2. Initialize the StandardScaler\n","scaler = StandardScaler()\n","\n","# 3. Apply the scaling to the continuous features\n","# We fit and transform the data in one step\n","df_final[continuous_features] = scaler.fit_transform(df_final[continuous_features])\n","\n","# 4. Final Data Integrity Check\n","print(\"Data Normalization Complete.\")\n","print(\"\\nMean and Standard Deviation after scaling (should be ~0 and ~1):\")\n","for feat in continuous_features:\n","    print(f\"{feat.ljust(25)} | Mean: {df_final[feat].mean():.2f} | Std: {df_final[feat].std():.2f}\")\n","\n","# 5. Save the final processed dataset for the modeling phase\n","final_save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_ready_for_model.csv'\n","df_final.to_csv(final_save_path, index=False)\n","\n","print(f\"\\nSuccess! Your preprocessed dataset is saved at: {final_save_path}\")"],"metadata":{"id":"4Qb64sLW2p4q","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390654202,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":4009,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"0cb85b54-dbdd-42ff-c90b-892ac91218ff"},"execution_count":10,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Data Normalization Complete.\n","\n","Mean and Standard Deviation after scaling (should be ~0 and ~1):\n","ms_first_response_time    | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","past_attempts             | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","past_successes            | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","historical_accuracy       | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","item_difficulty           | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","gamification_score        | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","magic_hint_count          | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","\n","Success! Your preprocessed dataset is saved at: /content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_ready_for_model.csv\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Etape 7 : la distribution du nombre d'interactions par utilisateur"],"metadata":{"id":"dq1QHsDvuTM2"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Justifier statistiquement la conception de notre modèle. En générant un histogramme, nous démontrons que la médiane des exercices complétés par élève est de 23. Cela prouve scientifiquement que notre choix de limiter la mémoire séquentielle de l'IA à 50 interactions (MAX_SEQ_LEN) est optimal.*"],"metadata":{"id":"UawNK33DBOAE"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# 1. Calculate the number of interactions per student in the final dataset\n","interactions_per_student = df_final.groupby('user_id').size()\n","\n","# 2. Display descriptive statistics (Median, mean, percentiles)\n","print(\"--- Statistics of interactions per student ---\")\n","print(interactions_per_student.describe(percentiles=[0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 0.90, 0.95]))\n","\n","# 3. Plot an histogram to visualize the actual data distribution\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n","plt.hist(interactions_per_student, bins=50, range=(0, 200), color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')\n","\n","# Add vertical lines for the median and your current choice of 50\n","median_val = interactions_per_student.median()\n","plt.axvline(median_val, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_val}')\n","plt.axvline(50, color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Current Choice (MAX_SEQ_LEN): 50')\n","\n","plt.title(\"Distribution of the Number of Interactions per Student (Capped at 200)\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Number of Interactions (Exercises Completed)\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Students\")\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"R7e8ojO0sbxA","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":695},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390654517,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":213,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"9fc9eb65-3b21-42eb-91c9-75ee8cee5e11"},"execution_count":11,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["--- Statistics of interactions per student ---\n","count    4437.000000\n","mean       44.773946\n","std        61.063055\n","min         1.000000\n","25%        10.000000\n","50%        23.000000\n","75%        54.000000\n","90%       113.000000\n","95%       168.200000\n","max       509.000000\n","dtype: float64\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ce graphique montre que la majorité des étudiants font relativement peu d'exercices, puisque la moitié d'entre eux en terminent moins de 23 (la ligne rouge). Notre limite fixée à 50 interactions (la ligne verte) est donc un très bon choix : elle permet à notre IA d'analyser le parcours complet de la grande majorité des élèves sans ralentir le système avec des calculs inutiles."],"metadata":{"id":"4GVDCcPICLkT"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 8:  Le Partitionnement Temporel (Temporal ou Chronological Split)**"],"metadata":{"id":"eIh01AdbYjGQ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Séparer la ligne du temps en trois époques : le Passé pour entraîner le modèle (Train : 60%), le Présent pour la valider (Baseline : 15%), et le Futur pour la tester (Drift : 25%). Dans le bloc Futur, le code agit comme un laboratoire : il sabote volontairement les données en transformant les questions faciles en échecs. C'est l'injection artificielle de la dérive conceptuelle*"],"metadata":{"id":"CffEZFnRHaM6"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. LOAD AND SORT CHRONOLOGICALLY\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"Loading dataset...\")\n","df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_ready_for_model.csv')\n","\n","# Absolute rule: Sort by order_id to simulate the real passage of time\n","df = df.sort_values(by='order_id').reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","total_interactions = len(df)\n","print(f\"Total interactions: {total_interactions}\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. CHRONOLOGICAL SPLIT (TIME-SPLIT)\n","# ==========================================\n","# Calculate cutoff indices for Train (60%), Baseline (15%), Drift (25%)\n","train_end_idx = int(total_interactions * 0.60)\n","baseline_end_idx = train_end_idx + int(total_interactions * 0.15)\n","\n","# Block A: The Past (60%) -> Used to train the AI\n","df_train = df.iloc[:train_end_idx].copy()\n","\n","# Block B: The Present (15%) -> Used to validate normal behavior (Baseline)\n","df_baseline = df.iloc[train_end_idx:baseline_end_idx].copy()\n","\n","# Block C: The Future (25%) -> Used as a laboratory for Concept Drift\n","df_drift = df.iloc[baseline_end_idx:].copy()\n","\n","print(\"\\nData splitting completed:\")\n","print(f\" - Train Block    : {len(df_train)} rows\")\n","print(f\" - Baseline Block : {len(df_baseline)} rows\")\n","print(f\" - Drift Block    : {len(df_drift)} rows\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","## ==========================================\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. SEMANTIC CONCEPT DRIFT: EASY QUESTIONS REFORM\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n--- Concept Drift Preparation ---\")\n","\n","# A. Identify the threshold for the 30% \"easiest\" exercises in the Drift block\n","easy_threshold = df_drift['item_difficulty'].quantile(0.30)\n","\n","# B. Target the rows where the exercise was \"easy\" AND where the student succeeded\n","trick_mask = (df_drift['item_difficulty'] <= easy_threshold) & (df_drift['correct'] == 1)\n","infected_indices = df_drift[trick_mask].index\n","\n","# C. THE INJECTION: Force the failure\n","df_drift.loc[infected_indices, 'correct'] = 0\n","\n","# Note: We do not manually modify the 'gamification_score' here, because the column\n","# was already normalized by StandardScaler in Step 6.\n","\n","print(f\" Semantic drift successfully injected on {len(infected_indices)} interactions!\")\n","print(\" -> Successes on historically easy questions became failures (Trick questions).\")\n","\n","# Save the three blocks separately to Google Drive\n","folder_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","df_train.to_csv(folder_path + 'train_block.csv', index=False)\n","df_baseline.to_csv(folder_path + 'baseline_block.csv', index=False)\n","df_drift.to_csv(folder_path + 'drift_block.csv', index=False)\n","\n","print(\"The 3 parts were successfully saved!\")\n","\n","# 4. Display the summary for tracking\n","print(f\" Drift successfully injected on {len(infected_indices)} interactions!\")\n","print(\" -> The answers were changed to 0 (Failure).\")\n","print(\" -> The gamification score was penalized by -15 points for these errors.\")\n","\n","# Display the summary\n","print(f\"Massive injection: {len(infected_indices)} successes on 'medium' items became failures.\")"],"metadata":{"id":"5JRSxKwxY3k8","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390658964,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":4432,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"33b6e567-a657-4d80-a32a-fd3504c5d785"},"execution_count":12,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading dataset...\n","Total interactions: 198662\n","\n","Data splitting completed:\n"," - Train Block    : 119197 rows\n"," - Baseline Block : 29799 rows\n"," - Drift Block    : 49666 rows\n","\n","--- Concept Drift Preparation ---\n"," Semantic drift successfully injected on 12250 interactions!\n"," -> Successes on historically easy questions became failures (Trick questions).\n","The 3 parts were successfully saved!\n"," Drift successfully injected on 12250 interactions!\n"," -> The answers were changed to 0 (Failure).\n"," -> The gamification score was penalized by -15 points for these errors.\n","Massive injection: 12250 successes on 'medium' items became failures.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## **Etape 9 :Séquençage et Tensorisation **"],"metadata":{"id":"D1G3Sg_YueAU"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** Transformer les données tabulaires 2D en blocs 3D (Tenseurs PyTorch). Les réseaux de neurones récurrents comme le xLSTM exigent un format séquentiel (Utilisateur, Temps, Variables). Le code comble les vides avec des zéros (Padding) pour harmoniser les séquences."],"metadata":{"id":"cMAduU2m_dOU"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import torch\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 0. LOADING SAVED FILES\n","# ==========================================\n","load_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","print(\"Loading blocks from Google Drive...\")\n","\n","# Importing the 3 blocks you saved in the previous step\n","df_train = pd.read_csv(load_path + 'train_block.csv')\n","df_baseline = pd.read_csv(load_path + 'baseline_block.csv')\n","df_drift = pd.read_csv(load_path + 'drift_block.csv')\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. PARAMETERS & COLUMNS (FIXED)\n","# ==========================================\n","MAX_SEQ_LEN = 50\n","target_col = 'correct'\n","\n","# Add ALL non-numerical columns here\n","cols_to_exclude = [\n","    'order_id', 'assignment_id', 'user_id', 'assistment_id',\n","    'problem_id', 'sequence_id', 'base_sequence_id', target_col,\n","    'list_skills'  # <--- This is the column that was blocking everything!\n","]\n","\n","feature_cols = [col for col in df_train.columns if col not in cols_to_exclude]\n","print(f\"Number of features injected per sequence: {len(feature_cols)}\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. SEQUENCING FUNCTION (Padding/Truncating)\n","# ==========================================\n","def process_user_sequence(user_df):\n","    user_df = user_df.sort_values('order_id')\n","    x_user = user_df[feature_cols].values\n","    y_user = user_df[target_col].values\n","\n","    if len(x_user) > MAX_SEQ_LEN:\n","        x_user = x_user[-MAX_SEQ_LEN:]\n","        y_user = y_user[-MAX_SEQ_LEN:]\n","    elif len(x_user) < MAX_SEQ_LEN:\n","        pad_length = MAX_SEQ_LEN - len(x_user)\n","        pad_x = np.zeros((pad_length, len(feature_cols)))\n","        x_user = np.vstack((pad_x, x_user))\n","        pad_y = np.full((pad_length,), -1)\n","        y_user = np.concatenate((pad_y, y_user))\n","\n","    return x_user, y_user\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. ENCAPSULATION FOR TEMPORAL SEPARATION\n","# ==========================================\n","def dataframe_to_tensors(df_block, block_name):\n","    print(f\"\\nSequencing block: {block_name}...\")\n","    sequences = df_block.groupby('user_id').apply(process_user_sequence, include_groups=False)\n","\n","    X_3D = np.stack(sequences.apply(lambda x: x[0]).values)\n","    y_2D = np.stack(sequences.apply(lambda x: x[1]).values)\n","\n","    X_tensor = torch.tensor(X_3D, dtype=torch.float32)\n","    y_tensor = torch.tensor(y_2D, dtype=torch.float32)\n","\n","    print(f\"{block_name} completed! Shape X: {X_tensor.shape}, Shape y: {y_tensor.shape}\")\n","    return X_tensor, y_tensor\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. EXECUTION AND SAVING\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n Starting tensorization...\")\n","\n","X_train_tensor, y_train_tensor = dataframe_to_tensors(df_train, \"TRAIN\")\n","X_baseline_tensor, y_baseline_tensor = dataframe_to_tensors(df_baseline, \"BASELINE\")\n","X_drift_tensor, y_drift_tensor = dataframe_to_tensors(df_drift, \"DRIFT\")\n","\n","# Save tensors ready for PyTorch\n","torch.save(X_train_tensor, load_path + 'X_train_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(y_train_tensor, load_path + 'y_train_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(X_baseline_tensor, load_path + 'X_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(y_baseline_tensor, load_path + 'y_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(X_drift_tensor, load_path + 'X_drift_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(y_drift_tensor, load_path + 'y_drift_tensor.pt')\n","\n","print(f\"\\n Tensors safely saved in: {load_path}\")"],"metadata":{"id":"FmKGEwtmucfo","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390667698,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":8706,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"56919c26-0a85-4910-da73-aa4aab50eb20"},"execution_count":13,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading blocks from Google Drive...\n","Number of features injected per sequence: 18\n","\n"," Starting tensorization...\n","\n","Sequencing block: TRAIN...\n","TRAIN completed! Shape X: torch.Size([3345, 50, 18]), Shape y: torch.Size([3345, 50])\n","\n","Sequencing block: BASELINE...\n","BASELINE completed! Shape X: torch.Size([1642, 50, 18]), Shape y: torch.Size([1642, 50])\n","\n","Sequencing block: DRIFT...\n","DRIFT completed! Shape X: torch.Size([2190, 50, 18]), Shape y: torch.Size([2190, 50])\n","\n"," Tensors safely saved in: /content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 10 : Entrainement (Train)**"],"metadata":{"id":"X5153GyyE1B-"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Définir l'architecture mathématique des couches du xLSTM. Ensuite, le code lance la phase d'apprentissage exclusivement sur les données du Passé (Train) pendant 10 cycles (epochs), puis sauvegarde le \"cerveau\" résultant sous le nom reliable_xlstm_model.pth.*"],"metadata":{"id":"Xfq-dAJd_kDD"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import torch.optim as optim\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. STABILIZED xLSTM LAYER\n","# ==========================================\n","class xLSTMLayer(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):\n","        super(xLSTMLayer, self).__init__()\n","        self.hidden_size = hidden_size\n","        self.W = nn.Linear(input_size, 4 * hidden_size)\n","        self.U = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 4 * hidden_size)\n","\n","    def forward(self, x):\n","        batch_size, seq_len, _ = x.size()\n","        h = torch.zeros(batch_size, self.hidden_size).to(x.device)\n","        c = torch.zeros(batch_size, self.hidden_size).to(x.device)\n","\n","        outputs = []\n","        for t in range(seq_len):\n","            xt = x[:, t, :]\n","            gates = self.W(xt) + self.U(h)\n","            i, f, o, g = gates.chunk(4, 1)\n","\n","            i = torch.exp(torch.clamp(i, max=20))\n","            f = torch.sigmoid(f)\n","            o = torch.sigmoid(o)\n","            g = torch.tanh(g)\n","\n","            c = f * c + i * g\n","            c = torch.clamp(c, min=-1e5, max=1e5)\n","\n","            h = o * torch.tanh(c)\n","            outputs.append(h.unsqueeze(1))\n","\n","        return torch.cat(outputs, dim=1)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. MODEL AND LOSS\n","# ==========================================\n","class KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):\n","        super(KnowledgeTracingxLSTM, self).__init__()\n","        self.xlstm = xLSTMLayer(input_size, hidden_size)\n","        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 1)\n","\n","    def forward(self, x):\n","        out = self.xlstm(x)\n","        return self.fc(out).squeeze(-1)\n","\n","class MaskedBCELoss(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self):\n","        super(MaskedBCELoss, self).__init__()\n","        self.criterion = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss(reduction='none')\n","\n","    def forward(self, predictions, targets):\n","        loss = self.criterion(predictions, targets)\n","        mask = (targets != -1).float()\n","        return (loss * mask).sum() / (mask.sum() + 1e-8)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. DATA PREPARATION (TRAIN ONLY)\n","# ==========================================\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","# Exclusive loading of the Train block (60%)\n","X_train_tensor = torch.load(save_path + 'X_train_tensor.pt')\n","y_train_tensor = torch.load(save_path + 'y_train_tensor.pt')\n","\n","BATCH_SIZE = 32\n","train_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_train_tensor, y_train_tensor), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n","\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=X_train_tensor.shape[2], hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","criterion = MaskedBCELoss()\n","optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.0005)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. PURE TRAINING\n","# ==========================================\n","print(f\"🚀 Starting exclusive training on {device}...\")\n","model.train()\n","\n","for epoch in range(10):\n","    total_loss = 0\n","    for X_batch, y_batch in train_loader:\n","        X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","\n","        optimizer.zero_grad()\n","        preds = model(X_batch)\n","        loss = criterion(preds, y_batch)\n","\n","        if torch.isnan(loss):\n","            continue\n","\n","        loss.backward()\n","        torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)\n","        optimizer.step()\n","\n","        total_loss += loss.item()\n","\n","    avg_loss = total_loss / len(train_loader)\n","    print(f\"Epoch [{epoch+1}/10] | Training Loss: {avg_loss:.4f}\")\n","\n","# Final save\n","torch.save(model.state_dict(), save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth')\n","print(f\"\\n Model successfully trained and saved in: {save_path}reliable_xlstm_model.pth\")"],"metadata":{"id":"Q0XDlsFm54jg","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390720870,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":53169,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"outputId":"fae41de9-db79-4b32-dbe5-dc7483a10935"},"execution_count":14,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["🚀 Starting exclusive training on cuda...\n","Epoch [1/10] | Training Loss: 0.6225\n","Epoch [2/10] | Training Loss: 0.5234\n","Epoch [3/10] | Training Loss: 0.4726\n","Epoch [4/10] | Training Loss: 0.4465\n","Epoch [5/10] | Training Loss: 0.4247\n","Epoch [6/10] | Training Loss: 0.4081\n","Epoch [7/10] | Training Loss: 0.3940\n","Epoch [8/10] | Training Loss: 0.3786\n","Epoch [9/10] | Training Loss: 0.3679\n","Epoch [10/10] | Training Loss: 0.3576\n","\n"," Model successfully trained and saved in: /content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/reliable_xlstm_model.pth\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 11 :l'Évaluation Baseline (les 15%)**"],"metadata":{"id":"Qv4icuyHEMrv"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Mesurer les performances de l'IA figée sur le bloc de données \"Présent\" (le monde normal). Cela établit les métriques de référence (Précision, Taux d'erreur, F1-Score) et génère une matrice de confusion prouvant que le modèle est compétent.*"],"metadata":{"id":"HSxuXbST_r1-"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import numpy as np\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, f1_score, roc_auc_score\n","import seaborn as sns\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. LOADING BASELINE BLOCK ONLY\n","# ==========================================\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","print(\"Loading Baseline tensor...\")\n","X_baseline = torch.load(save_path + 'X_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","y_baseline = torch.load(save_path + 'y_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","\n","baseline_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_baseline, y_baseline), batch_size=32, shuffle=False)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. MODEL LOADING AND EVALUATION\n","# ==========================================\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=X_baseline.shape[2], hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","model.load_state_dict(torch.load(save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth'))\n","model.eval()\n","\n","all_targets = []\n","all_probs = []\n","\n","with torch.no_grad():\n","    for X_batch, y_batch in baseline_loader:\n","        X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","        outputs = model(X_batch)\n","\n","        # Mask to ignore padding (-1)\n","        mask = (y_batch != -1)\n","\n","        all_targets.extend(y_batch[mask].cpu().numpy())\n","        all_probs.extend(torch.sigmoid(outputs[mask]).cpu().numpy())\n","\n","# --- METRICS CALCULATION ---\n","targets = np.array(all_targets)\n","probs = np.array(all_probs)\n","preds = (probs > 0.5).astype(float)\n","\n","acc = (targets == preds).mean()\n","error_rate = 1 - acc\n","f1 = f1_score(targets, preds)\n","auc = roc_auc_score(targets, probs)\n","cm = confusion_matrix(targets, preds)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. RESULTS DISPLAY\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*40)\n","print(\"PERFORMANCE SUMMARY: BASELINE\")\n","print(\"=\"*40)\n","print(f\"Accuracy   : {acc*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"Error Rate : {error_rate*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"F1-Score   : {f1:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"AUC-ROC    : {auc:.4f}\")\n","\n","# Confusion Matrix Display\n","plt.figure(figsize=(5,4))\n","sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Greens',\n","            xticklabels=['Failure (0)', 'Success (1)'],\n","            yticklabels=['Failure (0)', 'Success (1)'])\n","plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix - Baseline\")\n","plt.ylabel('True Label')\n","plt.xlabel('Predicted Label')\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"_XpJWI-MEQZ4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390721798,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":925,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":566},"outputId":"a4d18f60-fb7d-4450-de38-19e60b53c86f"},"execution_count":15,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading Baseline tensor...\n","\n","========================================\n","PERFORMANCE SUMMARY: BASELINE\n","========================================\n","Accuracy   : 84.09%\n","Error Rate : 15.91%\n","F1-Score   : 0.8717\n","AUC-ROC    : 0.9009\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 500x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 12 : L'evaluation du bloc de dérive (Les 25%)**"],"metadata":{"id":"73bzvmxPzDk-"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Mesurer les performances de cet même modèle face au bloc \"Futur\" que nous avons volontairement infecté à l'étape 8. L'objectif est de quantifier l'effondrement des métriques (explosion du taux d'erreur et des faux positifs) face aux \"questions pièges\" que le modèle ne sait pas gérer.*"],"metadata":{"id":"MOBuGP8M_zUf"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import numpy as np\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, f1_score, roc_auc_score\n","import seaborn as sns\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. CONFIGURATION & LOADING THE DRIFT BLOCK\n","# ==========================================\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","print(\"Loading the Drift tensor...\")\n","X_drift = torch.load(save_path + 'X_drift_tensor.pt')\n","y_drift = torch.load(save_path + 'y_drift_tensor.pt')\n","\n","drift_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_drift, y_drift), batch_size=32, shuffle=False)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. MODEL LOADING AND PREDICTION\n","# ==========================================\n","# Dynamically retrieve the input dimension (e.g., 18 or 19 features)\n","input_dim = X_drift.shape[2]\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=input_dim, hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","model.load_state_dict(torch.load(save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth'))\n","model.eval()\n","\n","all_targets = []\n","all_probs = []\n","\n","print(\"Analyzing the Drift block...\")\n","with torch.no_grad():\n","    for X_batch, y_batch in drift_loader:\n","        X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","        outputs = model(X_batch)\n","\n","        # Mask to ignore padding (-1)\n","        mask = (y_batch != -1)\n","\n","        all_targets.extend(y_batch[mask].cpu().numpy())\n","        all_probs.extend(torch.sigmoid(outputs[mask]).cpu().numpy())\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. METRICS CALCULATION (ANOMALIES)\n","# ==========================================\n","targets = np.array(all_targets)\n","probs = np.array(all_probs)\n","preds = (probs > 0.5).astype(float)\n","\n","acc = (targets == preds).mean()\n","error_rate = 1 - acc  # Added to prevent a NameError during the print step\n","f1 = f1_score(targets, preds)\n","auc = roc_auc_score(targets, probs)\n","cm = confusion_matrix(targets, preds)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. RESULTS DISPLAY (FOR THE THESIS)\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"!\"*45)\n","print(\"RESULTS ON THE DRIFT BLOCK\")\n","print(\"!\"*45)\n","print(f\"Accuracy   : {acc*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"Error Rate : {error_rate*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"F1-Score   : {f1:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"AUC-ROC    : {auc:.4f}\")\n","\n","# Confusion Matrix Visualization\n","# We expect to see many False Positives (the model predicts 1 but the true label is 0)\n","plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))\n","sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Oranges',\n","            xticklabels=['Failure (0)', 'Success (1)'],\n","            yticklabels=['Failure (0)', 'Success (1)'])\n","plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix - Drift Block\")\n","plt.ylabel('True Label (Injected)')\n","plt.xlabel('Predicted Label (Frozen Model)')\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"5sv9r-W_z4wo","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390722975,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":1166,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":661},"outputId":"9f0fb95a-6b61-4013-9432-078684d282bf"},"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading the Drift tensor...\n","Analyzing the Drift block...\n","\n","!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n","RESULTS ON THE DRIFT BLOCK\n","!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n","Accuracy   : 60.60%\n","Error Rate : 39.40%\n","F1-Score   : 0.6136\n","AUC-ROC    : 0.6561\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x500 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **Etape 13:  Le Monitoring et la Double Alerte (Le Méta-Détecteur d'Ensemble)**"],"metadata":{"id":"qzq3UDbUINKo"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif :** *Simuler un déploiement en production. Le code fusionne le Présent et le Futur pour créer un flux de données continu. Il y branche deux capteurs statistiques : KSWIN (qui surveille la motivation de l'élève) et ADWIN (qui surveille l'erreur du modèle). L'objectif est de démontrer visuellement via un tableau de bord à double axe que le système est capable de détecter automatiquement le point de rupture.*"],"metadata":{"id":"GjtMDauDAIof"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ==========================================\n","# 0. PRIORITY INSTALLATION & IMPORTS\n","# ==========================================\n","!pip install river\n","\n","import random\n","import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","from river import drift\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 0.5. SET RANDOM SEED (SCIENTIFIC REPRODUCIBILITY)\n","# ==========================================\n","SEED = 42\n","\n","random.seed(SEED)\n","np.random.seed(SEED)\n","torch.manual_seed(SEED)\n","\n","if torch.cuda.is_available():\n","    torch.cuda.manual_seed(SEED)\n","    torch.cuda.manual_seed_all(SEED)\n","    torch.backends.cudnn.deterministic = True\n","    torch.backends.cudnn.benchmark = False\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. RECONSTRUCTION OF THE REAL TEMPORAL STREAM\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"Continuous evaluation: from the Past (Baseline) to the Future (Drift)...\")\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","# --- A. LOADING TENSORS AND MODEL ---\n","X_base, y_base = torch.load(save_path + 'X_baseline_tensor.pt'), torch.load(save_path + 'y_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","X_drift, y_drift = torch.load(save_path + 'X_drift_tensor.pt'), torch.load(save_path + 'y_drift_tensor.pt')\n","\n","loader_base = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_base, y_base), batch_size=32, shuffle=False)\n","loader_drift = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_drift, y_drift), batch_size=32, shuffle=False)\n","\n","# Reloading the model architecture\n","class xLSTMLayer(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):\n","        super(xLSTMLayer, self).__init__()\n","        self.hidden_size = hidden_size\n","        self.W = nn.Linear(input_size, 4 * hidden_size)\n","        self.U = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 4 * hidden_size)\n","\n","    def forward(self, x):\n","        batch_size, seq_len, _ = x.size()\n","        h = torch.zeros(batch_size, self.hidden_size).to(x.device)\n","        c = torch.zeros(batch_size, self.hidden_size).to(x.device)\n","        outputs = []\n","        for t in range(seq_len):\n","            xt = x[:, t, :]\n","            gates = self.W(xt) + self.U(h)\n","            i, f, o, g = gates.chunk(4, 1)\n","            i = torch.exp(torch.clamp(i, max=20))\n","            f = torch.sigmoid(f)\n","            o = torch.sigmoid(o)\n","            g = torch.tanh(g)\n","            c = f * c + i * g\n","            c = torch.clamp(c, min=-1e5, max=1e5)\n","            h = o * torch.tanh(c)\n","            outputs.append(h.unsqueeze(1))\n","        return torch.cat(outputs, dim=1)\n","\n","class KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):\n","        super(KnowledgeTracingxLSTM, self).__init__()\n","        self.xlstm = xLSTMLayer(input_size, hidden_size)\n","        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 1)\n","\n","    def forward(self, x):\n","        out = self.xlstm(x)\n","        return self.fc(out).squeeze(-1)\n","\n","input_dim = X_base.shape[2]\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=input_dim, hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","model.load_state_dict(torch.load(save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth'))\n","model.eval()\n","\n","# --- B. SECURE EXTRACTION ---\n","def get_predictions(loader):\n","    all_targets, all_preds = [], []\n","    with torch.no_grad():\n","        for X_batch, y_batch in loader:\n","            X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","            outputs = model(X_batch)\n","            mask = (y_batch != -1)\n","            all_targets.extend(y_batch[mask].cpu().numpy())\n","            probs = torch.sigmoid(outputs[mask]).cpu().numpy()\n","            all_preds.extend((probs > 0.5).astype(float))\n","    return np.array(all_targets), np.array(all_preds)\n","\n","targets_base, preds_base = get_predictions(loader_base)\n","targets_drift, preds_drift = get_predictions(loader_drift)\n","\n","# --- C. MERGING AND CORRECTION OF THE DOMAIN STREAM ---\n","base_errors = (targets_base != preds_base).astype(int)\n","drift_errors = (targets_drift != preds_drift).astype(int)\n","complete_error_stream = np.concatenate([base_errors, drift_errors])\n","\n","complete_target_stream = np.concatenate([targets_base, targets_drift])\n","\n","# THE CORRECTION: Calculate points in real-time (+10 if target=1, -5 if target=0)\n","gamification_points_stream = np.where(complete_target_stream == 1, 10, -5)\n","\n","drift_start_index = len(base_errors)\n","stream_length = len(complete_error_stream)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. DETECTION (ADWIN & KSWIN) ON THE CONTINUOUS STREAM\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"Launching SIAD on the continuous stream...\")\n","\n","adwin_detector = drift.ADWIN()\n","# Only one instance of KSWIN, properly seeded\n","kswin_detector = drift.KSWIN(alpha=0.005, window_size=1000, stat_size=300, seed=SEED)\n","\n","ml_alerts = []\n","domain_alerts = []\n","major_drifts = []\n","\n","for i in range(stream_length):\n","    adwin_detector.update(complete_error_stream[i])\n","    kswin_detector.update(gamification_points_stream[i])\n","\n","    if adwin_detector.drift_detected: ml_alerts.append(i)\n","    if kswin_detector.drift_detected: domain_alerts.append(i)\n","\n","    # SIAD Cross-correlation\n","    if len(ml_alerts) > 0 and len(domain_alerts) > 0:\n","        if abs(ml_alerts[-1] - domain_alerts[-1]) < 500 and i not in major_drifts:\n","            if i > drift_start_index:\n","                major_drifts.append(i)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. VISUALIZATION (PROFESSIONAL DASHBOARD)\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"Generating professional visual evidence...\")\n","\n","window_size = 500\n","smoothed_error = pd.Series(complete_error_stream).rolling(window=window_size).mean() * 100\n","smoothed_score = pd.Series(gamification_points_stream).rolling(window=window_size).mean()\n","\n","# --- Aesthetic Configuration ---\n","sns.set_context(\"paper\", font_scale=1.2)\n","sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n","\n","fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\n","\n","# --- Axis 1 (Left): Student Motivation (Average points earned) ---\n","color_motivation = '#2A9D8F'\n","ax1.set_xlabel('Interactions (Timeline)', fontweight='bold')\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Points Average (Motivation)', color=color_motivation, fontweight='bold')\n","line1, = ax1.plot(smoothed_score, color=color_motivation, linewidth=2.5, label=\"Student Motivation (Avg Points)\")\n","ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color_motivation)\n","\n","# --- Axis 2 (Right): AI Error Rate ---\n","ax2 = ax1.twinx()\n","color_error = '#E76F51'\n","ax2.set_ylabel('xLSTM Model Error Rate (%)', color=color_error, fontweight='bold')\n","line2, = ax2.plot(smoothed_error, color=color_error, linewidth=2.5, linestyle='-', label=\"Model Prediction Error\")\n","ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color_error)\n","\n","max_err = smoothed_error.max()\n","if pd.notna(max_err):\n","    ax2.set_ylim(0, max_err + 10)\n","\n","# --- BACKGROUND ZONES & EVENTS ---\n","ax1.axvspan(0, drift_start_index, color='#E9ECEF', alpha=0.5)\n","ax1.axvspan(drift_start_index, stream_length, color='#FDE2E4', alpha=0.4)\n","\n","# --- LE NOUVEAU CODE CORRIGÉ ---\n","ax1.axvline(x=drift_start_index, color='#343A40', linestyle='--', linewidth=2)\n","\n","\n","if len(major_drifts) > 0:\n","    idx_alert = major_drifts[0]\n","    ax1.axvline(x=idx_alert, color='#D62828', linestyle='-', linewidth=3)\n","\n","\n","# --- LEGEND & TITLES ---\n","lines = [line1, line2]\n","labels = [l.get_label() for l in lines]\n","ax1.legend(lines, labels, loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.15), ncol=2, frameon=True, shadow=True)\n","\n","plt.title(\" Concept Drift Detection \", fontweight='bold', fontsize=14, pad=15)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n","print(f\"Summary: SIAD analyzed {stream_length} synchronized interactions.\")\n","if len(major_drifts) > 0:\n","    print(f\"It officially confirmed the semantic drift at interaction n°{major_drifts[0]}.\")\n","else:\n","    print(\"No joint drift detected. Check your KSWIN/ADWIN thresholds.\")\n","print(\"=\"*60)\n","# À mettre juste après tes commandes de plot (bbox_inches='tight' supprime les marges blanches)\n","plt.savefig('drift_detection_plot.pdf', bbox_inches='tight', dpi=300)"],"metadata":{"id":"iae3xTXLIFjT","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":892},"outputId":"d34c5978-f5d2-4712-c8b2-27bc7b0c0aae","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390749863,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":26873,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}}},"execution_count":17,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Requirement already satisfied: river in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (0.23.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: numpy>=1.23.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from river) (2.0.2)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pandas<3.0.0,>=2.2.3 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from river) (2.3.3)\n","Requirement already satisfied: scipy<2.0.0,>=1.14.1 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from river) (1.16.3)\n","Requirement already satisfied: python-dateutil>=2.8.2 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from pandas<3.0.0,>=2.2.3->river) (2.9.0.post0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pytz>=2020.1 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from pandas<3.0.0,>=2.2.3->river) (2025.2)\n","Requirement already satisfied: tzdata>=2022.7 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from pandas<3.0.0,>=2.2.3->river) (2025.3)\n","Requirement already satisfied: six>=1.5 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from python-dateutil>=2.8.2->pandas<3.0.0,>=2.2.3->river) (1.17.0)\n","Continuous evaluation: from the Past (Baseline) to the Future (Drift)...\n","Launching SIAD on the continuous stream...\n","Generating professional visual evidence...\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","============================================================\n","Summary: SIAD analyzed 70323 synchronized interactions.\n","It officially confirmed the semantic drift at interaction n°27166.\n","============================================================\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 0 Axes>"]},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 14 : Audit et Classification Statistique de la Dérive (Test Z et $h$ de Cohen)**"],"metadata":{"id":"9AfyR5UQ1UY5"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Objectif de ce module :**\n","\n","Une fois qu'une anomalie a été signalée par notre Méta-Détecteur (SIAD), il est indispensable de vérifier la validité mathématique de cette alerte et de classifier la dynamique temporelle de la dérive (Abrupte, Graduelle ou Incrémentale). Au lieu de s'appuyer sur des seuils empiriques arbitraires, ce module utilise les standards de la statistique inférentielle moderne.\n","\n","**Méthodologie Scientifique :**\n","\n","L'audit s'effectue en comparant une fenêtre de données précédant l'alerte (le comportement historique) avec une fenêtre de données succédant à l'alerte (le nouveau comportement). Deux métriques internationales sont calculées :\n","\n","\n","1. **La Significativité Statistique (Test Z pour deux proportions) :** L'algorithme calcule la p-value pour vérifier si la différence de taux d'erreur entre le passé et le futur est réelle. Une p-value inférieure à 0.05 prouve avec un niveau de confiance de 95% que la dégradation du modèle n'est pas due à une simple fluctuation aléatoire (bruit), mais bien à un changement d'état (Concept Drift)\n","2. **La Taille de l'Effet (Le $h$ de Cohen) :**\n","Une fois la dérive confirmée par le Test Z, sa \"violence\" (magnitude) est mesurée à l'aide de la transformation angulaire de Cohen (1988). Les seuils mondiaux du $h$ de Cohen nous permettent de classifier formellement la vitesse de la dérive :\n","\n","\n","*   $h \\ge 0.80$ (Effet massif) : Caractérise une Dérive Abrupte (Sudden Drift).\n","*   $0.20 \\le h < 0.80$ (Effet modéré) : Caractérise une Dérive Graduelle (Gradual Drift).\n","*   $h < 0.20$ (Effet marginal) : Caractérise une Dérive Incrémentale (Incremental Drift).\n","\n","\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"wmKl1DuwAUYG"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ==========================================\n","# 0. INSTALLATION & STATISTICAL IMPORTS\n","# ==========================================\n","!pip install statsmodels\n","\n","import numpy as np\n","import json\n","import datetime\n","from statsmodels.stats.proportion import proportions_ztest\n","\n","# Ensure we use the exact variables generated by Step 12\n","raw_error_data = complete_error_stream\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. CLASSIFICATION MODULE (Z-TEST & COHEN'S h)\n","# ==========================================\n","def classify_statistical_drift(raw_error_stream, alert_index, window=500):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Classifies the concept drift using international statistical standards:\n","    - Z-Test to prove statistical significance (p-value < 0.05).\n","    - Cohen's h (Effect Size) to measure severity (Sudden vs Gradual).\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if alert_index < window or (alert_index + window) > len(raw_error_stream):\n","        return \"Undetermined (Not enough data)\", 0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, \"N/A\"\n","\n","    # Extract temporal windows (Past vs Future)\n","    window_before = raw_error_stream[alert_index - window : alert_index]\n","    window_after = raw_error_stream[alert_index : alert_index + window]\n","\n","    # Calculate error rates (proportions)\n","    p1 = np.mean(window_before)\n","    p2 = np.mean(window_after)\n","\n","    # 1. SIGNIFICANCE TEST (Z-Test for two proportions)\n","    errors = np.array([np.sum(window_before), np.sum(window_after)])\n","    sizes = np.array([window, window])\n","\n","    # Calculate the p-value\n","    stat, p_value = proportions_ztest(errors, sizes)\n","\n","    # 2. EFFECT SIZE CALCULATION (Cohen's h)\n","    # We add a small epsilon (1e-5) to prevent math errors if p = 0 or 1\n","    arcsin_p1 = 2 * np.arcsin(np.sqrt(np.clip(p1, 1e-5, 1 - 1e-5)))\n","    arcsin_p2 = 2 * np.arcsin(np.sqrt(np.clip(p2, 1e-5, 1 - 1e-5)))\n","    cohen_h = abs(arcsin_p2 - arcsin_p1)\n","\n","    # 3. CLASSIFICATION BASED ON COHEN'S STANDARDS\n","    if p_value > 0.05:\n","        time_class = \"FALSE ALERT (Non-significant)\"\n","        details = \"The mathematical difference is due to chance (p-value > 0.05).\"\n","    else:\n","        if cohen_h >= 0.80:\n","            time_class = \"SUDDEN DRIFT\"\n","            details = \"Abrupt rupture validated by a massive statistical effect (Cohen's h >= 0.80).\"\n","        elif cohen_h >= 0.20:\n","            time_class = \"GRADUAL DRIFT\"\n","            details = \"Marked but non-instantaneous transition (0.20 <= h < 0.80).\"\n","        else:\n","            time_class = \"INCREMENTAL DRIFT\"\n","            details = \"Very slow obsolescence, marginal statistical effect (h < 0.20).\"\n","\n","    return time_class, cohen_h, p1, p2, p_value, details\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. EXECUTION AND SCIENTIFIC REPORT GENERATION\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"Starting Statistical Drift Audit...\")\n","\n","if 'major_drifts' in locals() and len(major_drifts) > 0:\n","    critical_alert = major_drifts[0]\n","\n","    time_class, cohen_h, err_bef, err_aft, p_val, details = classify_statistical_drift(\n","        raw_error_stream=raw_error_data,\n","        alert_index=critical_alert,\n","        window=500\n","    )\n","\n","    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*75)\n","    print(\"OFFICIAL SIAD CLASSIFICATION REPORT (2026 Standard)\")\n","    print(\"=\"*75)\n","    print(f\"Alert Point (Interaction)      : n°{critical_alert}\")\n","    print(f\"Historical Error Rate          : {err_bef*100:.2f}%\")\n","    print(f\"New Error Rate                 : {err_aft*100:.2f}%\")\n","    print(\"-\" * 75)\n","    print(\"STATISTICAL EVIDENCE (International MLOps Standards):\")\n","    print(f\"   - P-Value (Z-Test)          : {p_val:.5e} (Significant if < 0.05)\")\n","    print(f\"   - Effect Size (Cohen's h)   : {cohen_h:.3f} (Sudden Standard >= 0.8)\")\n","    print(\"-\" * 75)\n","    print(f\"TEMPORAL DIAGNOSIS             : {time_class}\")\n","    print(f\"Agent Analysis                 : {details}\")\n","    print(\"=\"*75)\n","\n","    # ==========================================\n","    # 3. ENHANCED JSON EXPORT (FOR SUBJECT 2)\n","    # ==========================================\n","    # We check for XAI metadata variables (real_user_id and translated_feature)\n","    # If they are not yet defined in the scope, we use default/detected values\n","    current_user_id = real_user_id if 'real_user_id' in locals() else 99999\n","    root_cause = translated_feature if 'translated_feature' in locals() else \"Unknown Concept Shift\"\n","\n","    # Determine the suggested LoRA strategy based on the drift class\n","    suggested_strategy = \"New LoRA Adapter\" if time_class == \"SUDDEN DRIFT\" else \"Adapter Fine-tuning\"\n","\n","    alert_payload = {\n","        \"status\": {\n","            \"drift_detected\": True,\n","            \"interaction_index\": int(critical_alert),\n","            \"timestamp\": datetime.datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\n","        },\n","        \"statistical_analysis\": {\n","            \"drift_type\": time_class,\n","            \"severity_score\": round(float(cohen_h), 4),\n","            \"p_value\": float(p_val),\n","            \"confidence_level\": 0.95\n","        },\n","        \"xai_metadata\": {\n","            \"root_cause_feature\": root_cause,\n","            \"impact_on_accuracy\": round(float(err_bef - err_aft), 4),\n","            \"affected_user_id\": int(current_user_id)\n","        },\n","        \"adaptation_recommendation\": {\n","            \"suggested_strategy\": suggested_strategy,\n","            \"learning_rate_scale\": \"High\" if cohen_h >= 0.5 else \"Low\"\n","        }\n","    }\n","\n","    # Define the export path\n","    export_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/drift_alert.json'\n","\n","    # Save the JSON file\n","    with open(export_path, 'w') as file:\n","        json.dump(alert_payload, file, indent=4)\n","\n","    print(f\"\\n✅ Standardized JSON alert generated at: {export_path}\")\n","    print(\"Ready for Subject 2 Adaptation Module.\")\n","\n","else:\n","    print(\"The system is stable. No major drift to classify or export.\")"],"metadata":{"id":"HWe1PgAY1PYt","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775390761622,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":11704,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"outputId":"523c109e-95c9-4eab-9377-a70c